# 2. Load & preprocess data
df = (
    pd.read_csv("bird_migration.csv")
      .drop(columns="Unnamed: 0", errors="ignore")
)
df["date_time"]   = pd.to_datetime(df["date_time"])
df["day_of_year"] = df["date_time"].dt.dayofyear
df["month"]       = df["date_time"].dt.month
df["bird_idx"]    = df["bird_name"].astype("category").cat.codes
n_birds = df["bird_idx"].nunique()

# Observations for daily means
daily   = df.groupby("day_of_year")["altitude"].mean().reset_index()
t       = daily["day_of_year"].values
y_daily = daily["altitude"].values

# Raw observations & seasonal angle
y_obs = df["altitude"].values
theta = 2 * np.pi * df["day_of_year"].values / 365.0

# 4. Seasonal vs. Null Models with weakly informative priors

# 4A. Seasonal model
with pm.Model() as seasonal_model:
    mu     = pm.StudentT("mu", nu=3, mu=0, sigma=10)
    beta_s = pm.Normal("beta_s", 0, 20)
    beta_c = pm.Normal("beta_c", 0, 20)
    sigma  = pm.HalfNormal("sigma", 10)
    mu_t   = mu + beta_s * np.sin(2*np.pi*t/365) + beta_c * np.cos(2*np.pi*t/365)
    pm.Normal("y_obs", mu=mu_t, sigma=sigma, observed=y_daily)

    idata_season = pm.sample(
        draws=1000, tune=1000, chains=4, cores=4,
        target_accept=0.95, random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=True,
        idata_kwargs={"log_likelihood": True}
    )

# 4B. Null model
with pm.Model() as null_model:
    mu0    = pm.StudentT("mu0", nu=3, mu=0, sigma=10)
    sigma0 = pm.HalfNormal("sigma0", 10)
    pm.Normal("y0", mu=mu0, sigma=sigma0, observed=y_daily)

    idata_null = pm.sample(
        draws=1000, tune=1000, chains=4, cores=4,
        target_accept=0.95, random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=True,
        idata_kwargs={"log_likelihood": True}
    )

# 7. Bayesian R² and PPC for seasonal model

# 7.1 Posterior predictive samples
with seasonal_model:
    ppc_season = pm.sample_posterior_predictive(
        idata_season,
        var_names=["y_obs"],
        random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=True
    )

# 7.2 Stack draws into shape (n_samples, n_obs)
y_pred_arr = (
    ppc_season.posterior_predictive["y_obs"]
      .stack(sample=("chain","draw"))
      .values
)
if y_pred_arr.shape[0] == y_daily.size:
    y_pred_arr = y_pred_arr.T

# 7.3 Compute Bayesian R²
r2_s = az.r2_score(y_daily, y_pred_arr)
print(f"Bayesian R² (seasonal): {r2_s['r2']:.3f} ± {r2_s['r2_std']:.3f}")

# 7.4 Plot PPC mean and 95% CI
ppc_mean = y_pred_arr.mean(axis=0)
ci_low   = np.percentile(y_pred_arr, 2.5, axis=0)
ci_high  = np.percentile(y_pred_arr, 97.5, axis=0)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))
plt.plot(t, y_daily, "o", alpha=0.4, label="Observed")
plt.plot(t, ppc_mean, "-", label="PPC Mean")
plt.fill_between(t, ci_low, ci_high, alpha=0.3, label="95% CI")
plt.title("Posterior Predictive Check: Seasonal Model")
plt.xlabel("Day of Year"); plt.ylabel("Altitude (m)")
plt.legend(); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()


# %%
# 8. Residual diagnostics
resid = y_daily - ppc_mean

plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
plt.scatter(ppc_mean, resid, alpha=0.6)
plt.axhline(0, linestyle="--", color="k")
plt.xlabel("Fitted"); plt.ylabel("Residuals")
plt.title("Residuals vs Fitted (Seasonal)")
plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

stats.probplot(resid, dist="norm", plot=plt)
plt.title("QQ Plot of Residuals (Seasonal)")
plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

# 9. Prior predictive check
with pm.Model() as prior_model:
    mu_p     = pm.Normal("mu", 0, 100)
    beta_s_p = pm.Normal("beta_s", 0, 50)
    beta_c_p = pm.Normal("beta_c", 0, 50)
    sigma_p  = pm.HalfNormal("sigma", 50)
    mu_t_p   = mu_p + beta_s_p*np.sin(theta) + beta_c_p*np.cos(theta)
    y_prior  = pm.Normal("y_prior", mu=mu_t_p, sigma=sigma_p, shape=y_obs.size)

    # return a simple dict for easy indexing
    prior_pred = pm.sample_prior_predictive(
        samples=30,
        random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=False
    )

# now prior_pred["y_prior"] is shape (30, n_obs)
y_prior_arr = prior_pred["y_prior"]
plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))
for draw in y_prior_arr:
    plt.plot(df["day_of_year"], draw, color="C1", alpha=0.1)
plt.title("Prior Predictive Draws"); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

# 10. Hierarchical model with random slopes

agg       = df.groupby(["bird_idx","day_of_year"])["altitude"].mean().reset_index()
y_agg     = agg["altitude"].values
idx_agg   = agg["bird_idx"].values
theta_agg = 2 * np.pi * agg["day_of_year"].values / 365.0

with pm.Model() as hier_slopes:
    # Hyperpriors
    mu_int    = pm.Normal("mu_int", 0, 10)
    sigma_int = pm.HalfNormal("sigma_int", 5)
    mu_s      = pm.Normal("mu_s", 0, 10)
    sigma_s   = pm.HalfNormal("sigma_s", 5)
    mu_c      = pm.Normal("mu_c", 0, 10)
    sigma_c   = pm.HalfNormal("sigma_c", 5)

    # Offsets & random effects
    int_off = pm.Normal("int_off", 0, 1, shape=n_birds)
    s_off   = pm.Normal("s_off",   0, 1, shape=n_birds)
    c_off   = pm.Normal("c_off",   0, 1, shape=n_birds)

    b_int = pm.Deterministic("b_int", mu_int + sigma_int*int_off)
    b_s   = pm.Deterministic("b_s",   mu_s   + sigma_s  *s_off)
    b_c   = pm.Deterministic("b_c",   mu_c   + sigma_c  *c_off)

    sigma_h = pm.HalfNormal("sigma", 10)
    mu_t_h  = (
        b_int[idx_agg]
      + b_s[idx_agg] * np.sin(theta_agg)
      + b_c[idx_agg] * np.cos(theta_agg)
    )

    pm.Normal("y", mu=mu_t_h, sigma=sigma_h, observed=y_agg)

    idata_hier = pm.sample(
        draws=800, tune=800, chains=4, cores=4,
        target_accept=0.95, init="adapt_diag",
        random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=True,
        idata_kwargs={"log_likelihood": True}
    )

# Diagnostics & LOO for hierarchical
print(az.summary(idata_hier, hdi_prob=0.95))
print("LOO:", az.loo(idata_hier))

with hier_slopes:
    ppc_hier = pm.sample_posterior_predictive(
        idata_hier,
        var_names=["y"],
        random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=True
    )

y_h_arr = (
    ppc_hier.posterior_predictive["y"]
      .stack(sample=("chain","draw"))
      .values
)
if y_h_arr.shape[0] == y_agg.size:
    y_h_arr = y_h_arr.T

r2_h = az.r2_score(y_agg, y_h_arr)
print(f"Bayesian R² (hierarchical): {r2_h['r2']:.3f} ± {r2_h['r2_std']:.3f}")

# 12. Circular model for flight direction

directions = df["direction"].dropna().values * np.pi/180  # radians
with pm.Model() as circ_dir:
    mu_dir = pm.VonMises("mu_dir", mu=0, kappa=1)
    kappa  = pm.HalfNormal("kappa", 5)
    pm.VonMises("obs_dir", mu=mu_dir, kappa=kappa, observed=directions)

    idata_dir = pm.sample(
        draws=100, tune=100, chains=4, cores=4,
        target_accept=0.9, random_seed=42,
        return_inferencedata=True
    )

print(az.summary(idata_dir, hdi_prob=0.95))
